Write a function createArray that takes a number n as an argument and returns an array containing natural numbers from 1 to a given number n: [1, 2, 3, ...., n].

If n = 0 return an empty array [].

Example:

createArray (3) return [1, 2, 3];
createArray (7) return [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7];
createArray (1) return [1];
createArray (0) return [].

Solution:

function createArray(n){
  let arr = [];
  for(let i = 1; i <= n ; i++) {
    arr.push(i);
  }
  return n === 0 ? [] : arr;
}
